From 53d0a8ecbb6796785282c1c7bdf324feda222c4d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Josua Mayer <josua@solid-run.com>
Date: Sat, 7 Mar 2026 14:04:49 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] lx2160acex7/lx2162asom: remove serdes equalization settings
 reduce size

Size of PBL is already massive due to large ARM errata.
Setting of equalization parameters further increases size by many bytes,
exceeding the limit of 4096 in some configurations.

Further if all lanes had their parameters set, limit would be exceeded
in all configurations.

Drop these settings, as they can be applied by U-Boot or Linux
alternatively.

Signed-off-by: Josua Mayer <josua@solid-run.com>
